From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Patric Stout <github@truebrain.nl>
Date: Sun, 5 Jul 2026 12:10:25 +0200
Subject: [PATCH 15/17] port(trinityal): add Vulkan backend for Linux

This is fully written by Claude's Fable + Opus 4.8.

The backend is far from done: not all functionality is supported,
and performance might be lacking. Use at your own risk.

Vulkan requires shaders to be exported in SPIR-V format. See
VulkanBindingModel.h for specification.
Your GPU needs to support dynamic rendering (either via Vulkan 1.3 or
via the extension). Dynamic rendering closest matches DX11/DX12/Metal,
making the port easier. A fallback is possible, but not implemented.

Missing components:
- Upscaling
